{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Increase the Category B driving license weight limit to 5000kg",
        "additional_details": "Reason being, a lot of modern motorhomes, and vans, especially Motorhomes with more berths, 4x4 systems, automatic transmission and other sundry accessories, look like your regular van, but many of them weigh over 3500kg, some knocking on for 4100kg.\r\nRaising the B limit would allow people who want to drive bigger vans (not just motorhomes) without the need to take the C1 license.\r\nIt would also allow people to drive bigger delivery vans also without the C1 license test",
        "background": "I think it would be great if the B license was increased to 5000kg.",
